{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.26",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 26,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 26 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:1",
      "text": "Like snow in summer, and as rain in harvest, so honor is not fitting for a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:2",
      "text": "Like a fluttering sparrow, like a darting swallow, so the undeserved curse doesn’t come to rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:3",
      "text": "A whip is for the horse, a bridle for the donkey, and a rod for the back of fools!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:4",
      "text": "Don’t answer a fool according to his folly, lest you also be like him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:5",
      "text": "Answer a fool according to his folly, lest he be wise in his own eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:6",
      "text": "One who sends a message by the hand of a fool is cutting off feet and drinking violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:7",
      "text": "Like the legs of the lame that hang loose, so is a parable in the mouth of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:8",
      "text": "As one who binds a stone in a sling, so is he who gives honor to a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:9",
      "text": "Like a thorn bush that goes into the hand of a drunkard, so is a parable in the mouth of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:10",
      "text": "As an archer who wounds all, so is he who hires a fool or he who hires those who pass by.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:11",
      "text": "As a dog that returns to his vomit, so is a fool who repeats his folly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:12",
      "text": "Do you see a man wise in his own eyes? There is more hope for a fool than for him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:13",
      "text": "The sluggard says, “There is a lion in the road! A fierce lion roams the streets!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:14",
      "text": "As the door turns on its hinges, so does the sluggard on his bed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:15",
      "text": "The sluggard buries his hand in the dish. He is too lazy to bring it back to his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:16",
      "text": "The sluggard is wiser in his own eyes than seven men who answer with discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:17",
      "text": "Like one who grabs a dog ’s ears is one who passes by and meddles in a quarrel not his own.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:18",
      "text": "Like a madman who shoots torches, arrows, and death,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:19",
      "text": "is the man who deceives his neighbor and says, “Am I not joking?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:20",
      "text": "For lack of wood a fire goes out. Without gossip, a quarrel dies down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:21",
      "text": "As coals are to hot embers, and wood to fire, so is a contentious man to kindling strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:22",
      "text": "The words of a whisperer are as dainty morsels, they go down into the innermost parts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:23",
      "text": "Like silver dross on an earthen vessel are the lips of a fervent one with an evil heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:24",
      "text": "A malicious man disguises himself with his lips, but he harbors evil in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:25",
      "text": "When his speech is charming, don’t believe him, for there are seven abominations in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:26",
      "text": "His malice may be concealed by deception, but his wickedness will be exposed in the assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:27",
      "text": "Whoever digs a pit shall fall into it. Whoever rolls a stone, it will come back on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.26.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 26:28",
      "text": "A lying tongue hates those it hurts; and a flattering mouth works ruin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
